OL,6,FThe defendants had each denied one
OL,7,Fcount of criminal damage but a jury
OL,8,Ffound them guilty after a trial in
OL,9,FAugust.
OL,11,FThe trial heard that the fountain,
OL,12,Fwhich is cleaned once a month,
OL,13,Freceived an emergency clean at an
OL,14,Fextra cost after the protest.
OL,16,FMichael Robert Turner, an assistant
OL,17,Fmanager for Royal Parks at the time of
OL,18,Fthe incident, told the jury the marble
OL,19,Fis "porous" and there was a risk the
OL,20,Fdye would seep in and stain the stone
OL,21,Fif it was not immediately cleaned.
